text: The Gabonese Football Federation (; FGF) is the governing body of football in Gabon. It is in charge of the men's and the women's national teams. The association was founded in 1962. It became a member of FIFA in 1963 and CAF in 1967. Category:1962 establishments in Africa Category:Football governing bodies in Africa Category:Football in Gabon
title: Gabonese Football Federation
